{
  "texts": [
    "As Figure A.9 shows, increasing the balance of the training sample leads to more reliable and consistent performance across all metrics.",
    "Notably, the model achieves its most balanced performance in terms of F1-score when the sample is well-balanced, indicating that a balanced dataset enables the model to capture relevant patterns more effectively.",
    "This observation aligns with established research in machine learning and neural networks, confirming the well-known importance of data balance in achieving optimal model performance (Miric et al., 2022).",
